<HEAD>Noriega Foes Move To Choke Panamanian Cash Flow, Freeze Assets in
US</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department says it approves of
efforts by opponents of Panamanian strongman Manuel Antonio Noriega
to freeze Panamanian assets in the United States and choke off
payments to the government.
   ``It's their action to take,'' State Department spokeswoman
Phyllis Oakley said Tuesday, calling it ``the legitimate action of
