<1ST_LINE>r w PM-GAO-Drugs     03-02 0404</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-GAO-Drugs,390</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>RETRANSMITTING to change cycle designator.</HEAD>
<HEAD>GAO Study: A Drug Overview</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Drug Wars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cocaine now is the most visible target in the
war on drugs, a battle that a congressional report says is costing
society tens of billions of dollars a year in lost wages, law
enforcement outlays and treatment programs.
   A study of recent changes in the drug trade by the General
Accounting Office, the investigative arm of Congress, said,
``Cocaine has emerged as the widely abused drug of greatest
concern.''
   Marijuana use has been declining, the report said, while various
substances known as designer drugs have emerged as a significant
phenomenon.
   Some highlights of ``Controlling Drug Abuse: A Status Report,''
include:
   _In 1983 alone, drugs cost American society some $59.7 billion
in crime, lost employment, criminal justice spending, prisons,
reduced productivity and treatment programs.
   _The number of cocaine-related emergencies reported by hospitals
jumped 167 percent from 1983 to 1986.
   _The share of high school seniors who admitted ever having used
cocaine fell from 16.9 percent in 1986 to 15.2 percent in 1987.
However, some experts fear this may not include all those using the
newly popular ``crack'' form of cocaine, which is smoked and is
highly popular among young people.
   _Heroin seems to be widely available across the country. The
number of heroin-related hospital emergencies rose 24 percent from
1983 to 1986.
   _Marijuana use has declined, although it remains the most widely
used illegal drug in the country. An estimated 61.9 million people
over age 12 have used this drug at least once.
   _Los Angeles is the cocaine consumption capital of the nation,
although PCP and heroin are also popular and it's a transshipment
point for Mexican heroin.
   _Miami is the cocaine importation center, with many homicides
related to the drug trade. The spread of the disease AIDS is being
added to by the use of drug needles.
   _New York has become a center for the importation of heroin and
has the nation's largest heroin addict population with the spread
of AIDS also a major problem. The New York heroin trade is
dominated by Chinese immigrants.
   _San Francisco faces a major problem with LSD and
methamphetamines, with growing use of heroin and cocaine.
   _Cocaine availability has increased sharply in Washington, D.C.,
where PCP also is used heavily. A high per capita overdose rate is
reported in the nation's capital.
   _Chicago too is facing rising cocaine use.
</TEXT>
