<HEAD>Elderly Man Buried Alive By Cinder Blocks; Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLANTATION, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Neighbors and police worked frantically
but failed to save an elderly man who was buried alive by cinder
blocks when he tried to demolish a 5-foot-high wall in his yard.
   Edward Margrabia, 69, died Tuesday of multiple trauma at
Pembroke Pines Hospital.
   ``He was just crushed, his kidneys and everything. Oh, I tell
you, it was awful,'' said neighbor Ann Adelson. ``Poor man. He's a
terrific guy. He helps everybody in the neighborhood.''
   Chris McCauley, whose home is behind Margrabia's, said she heard
the wall collapse as she fixed sandwiches for lunch.
   ``I just heard a sound like cement blocks hitting the ground ...
I thought it was strange to hear a noise and see nobody there,''
she said. When she realized what had happened, she roused other
neighbors to help extricate Margrabia.
   ``By the time we had eight people there, we were trying to pry
the wall up with pieces of wood. And as we were trying, the wall
broke _ right on his back,'' Ms. McCauley said.
   When police arrived to free Margrabia with a hydraulic jack, he
was unconscious, police spokesman Ed Plaisted said. Margrabia, who
was recovering from heart-bypass surgery, was trapped for about 30
minutes.
