<HEAD>Police Foil Plot to Abduct Multimillionaire's Son</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police today said they arrested a
couple who planned to kidnap the son of a wealthy businessman and
inject him with AIDS-infected blood unless a $350,000 ransom was
paid.
   Two vials of blood were found during a raid on the couple's home
in the northern part of New South Wales, police said.
   Detectives said they acted on an anonymous tip that the husband
and wife planned to abduct the 15-year-old son of a
multimillionaire businessman outside the youth's school.
   The businessman was not identified.
