<HEAD>Chinese Bus Plunges Into River, Killing 22</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus slid into a river at a ferry crossing in
southeastern China when its brakes failed, killing at least 22
people, according to a news report.
   The Hong Kong China News Service said Tuesday the accident
occurred about noon Saturday in Wuning county of Jiangxi province.
   The driver and five children were among the dead and two of the
63 passengers aboard the bus remained missing, said the news
agency, which quoted local security officials it did not identify.
