<HEAD>Bomb Damages Downtown Apartment Building</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A powerful bomb exploded in the
doorway of a downtown apartment building today, damaging property
but causing no injuries, federal police said.
   Police said the 1:50 a.m. blast at a four-story apartment
building blew a heavy wooden door into the street and shattered
windows in adjacent buildings.
   Police said the objective of the attack was not immediately
clear and that no political or military figures lived in the
building.
   Police said they found several leaflets at the scene bearing the
initials ``O.A.S.,'' ``M.R.P,'' and the phrase ``For National
Liberation,'' as well as drawings of Argentine independence hero
Gen. Jose de San Martin and a condor.
   The significance of the initials was not immediately known. No
known terrorist or extremist group has used those initials in
recent years.
