<DOCNO> AP880302-0169 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-02-88 1401EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Saudi-Stadium     03-02 0219</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Saudi-Stadium,0228</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>King Fahd Inaugurates Largest Free-Span Stadium</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   King Fahd on Wednesday inaugurated
the King Fahd International Stadium, the largest free-span
structure in the world.
   The official opening of the stadium coincided with the ninth
Gulf Cup Soccer Championships in which seven teams from Arab
countries are participating.
   In a ceremonial message, King Fahd said ``this is eloquent proof
of the progress which this country has made in all fields.''
   There have been hints in the pro-government media that the
kingdom would like to be a host for the Olympic Games.
   The multimillion-dollar stadium can accommodate 75,000
spectators, with the design owing something to the traditional
shape of a bedouin tent but merged with the most advanced
engineering technology.
   The exterior of the stadium is in the shape of a circle with a
diamater of 290 yards. The bowl contains the playing field with
natural grass, imported from Kenya, the 400-yard running track, the
long jump pits, pole vaulting area and javelin throw run.
   The roof membrane is stretched between 24 tent-shaped peaks,
each supported by a 60-yard vertical mast. The covering is a
Teflon-coated fabric.
   The royal and VIP pavilion, with six floors of exclusively
furnished rooms for royal receptions, seats 750.
   The grass is watered from a 15-inch-deep water underground
reservoir.
</TEXT>
