<HEAD>Ugandan Minister Shot By Car Thieves</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three people have been arrested in a
roadside robbery in which a deputy minister was shot, it was
reported Wednesday.
   Aggrey Suit, deputy minister for energy and technology, was
driving Tuesday with his 6-year-old daughter through a suburb of
Kampala when three gunmen drove from the roadside, blocked his
vehicle and demanded the keys, the government-owned Radio Uganda
said.
   During a scuffle, one of the gunmen opened fire hitting Suit in
the leg. The girl was not injured.
   The gunmen fled with Suit's four-wheel drive vehicle, which was
found abandoned at Jinja, 50 miles east of Kampala.
</TEXT>
