<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--PoisonSoybeans     03-02 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Poison Soybeans,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Death Toll In Food Poisoning Rises To 34</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: One name Koentoro is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eleven more people have died after
eating improperly prepared soybeans in the Central Java district of
Banyumas, bringing the death toll to 34, a medical official said
Wednesday.
   Koentoro, head of the district health office in Banyumas, said
the latest victims died Tuesday after eating soybean cakes
contaminated with poisonous acid. The poisonings occurred in
Dermaji, 300 miles southeast of Jakarta.
   A Health Ministry official in Jakarta said Tuesday that 260
people had been hospitalized in Dermaji over the past two weeks
after eating the soybean cakes, known locally as tempe bongkrek.
   The official said poverty had forced villagers to ignore a
government ban on eating the cheap food, which sometimes contains
the poisonous acid bongkrekik.
   Koentoro said 33 people still were hospitalized, some in grave
condition.
   Two people who allegedly produced and sold the cakes have been
arrested, the ministry official said.
</TEXT>
