<1ST_LINE>r a AM-HiddenEye     03-02 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Hidden Eye,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Surgery On Turkish Girl with Hidden Eye</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 7-year-old born with no external eyes underwent
surgery Wednesday in another of a series of operations to create
eyelids and sockets and allow her to see.
   Dilek Erdogan of Turkey was born with a nose and a mouth, ``and
that's it for her face,'' said Dr. Allen Putterman, who performed
the surgery at the University of Illinois Hospital Eye and Ear
Infirmary. Her eyes are below the skin.
   Dilek's left eye, which will always be sightless, will be
replaced with an artifical one, but doctors hope to enable her see
out of her right eye, Putterman said.
   In August, Putterman slit the skin over her right eye and placed
a temporary insert between the skin and the eye to create some
space around the eyeball. He then sewed the slit closed.
   On Wednesday, he reopened the slit and began forming an eyelid.
Putterman said he also began the insertion procedure on the left
eye.
   Dilek was bought to this country for treatment more than a year
ago.
</TEXT>
