<HEAD>South Korea Reports Wider Trade Surplus In February</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's trade surplus more than
tripled in February from a year earlier on the strength of exports,
the government reported Wednesday.
   The Trade and Industry Ministry said last month's surplus rose
to $524 million from $158 million in 1987. That brought the surplus
for the first two months of this year to $810 million from $683
million last year, it said.
   Exports in February rose 41 percent to $4.1 billion from, while
imports grew 30 percent to $3.57 billion.
   The ministry did not provide a breakdown by country.
   During 1987, South Korea posted a trade surplus of $6.26 billion.
